17:30.739 --> 17:32.639
Besides, didn't you organize
that Mexican

17:32.641 --> 17:34.140
children charity
or something?

17:34.142 --> 17:36.610
Look, I love helping
children in the abstract,

17:36.612 --> 17:38.878
but I don't want one
in the house.

17:38.880 --> 17:40.214
Hmm.

17:40.216 --> 17:41.948
Well, at any rate, we have
to send it to school.

17:41.950 --> 17:43.817
- Really?
- Yeah, it's the law.

17:43.819 --> 17:47.253
And it gets him out
of the house for the day.

18:05.541 --> 18:06.607
Hello.

18:06.609 --> 18:08.007
Oh, hello.

18:08.009 --> 18:10.244
We would like to enroll
this young man.

18:10.246 --> 18:14.817
All right.
And what is his name?

18:22.492 --> 18:24.694
Would you excuse us,
please?

18:30.666 --> 18:35.936
Oh, I see you've discovered
one of my favorite contraptions.

18:35.938 --> 18:40.507
These are such fun.
Let's have a look.

18:40.509 --> 18:44.678
Hmm. You might want to vary
your expression a bit.

18:44.680 --> 18:48.651
Scoot along.
Join in with me if you like.

18:49.884 --> 18:52.552
I like to do one happy...

18:52.554 --> 18:54.888
one angry...

18:54.890 --> 18:57.891
one silly...

18:57.893 --> 18:59.693
and one just looking off
into the middle distance,

18:59.695 --> 19:02.866
thinking
about something.

19:06.169 --> 19:08.838
Now we've got
a bit of an awkward wait.

19:11.907 --> 19:16.842
Oh, look at those.
We're hilarious.

19:16.844 --> 19:18.411
What would you like
to do now?

19:38.534 --> 19:40.402
Having a party?

19:41.536 --> 19:43.840
No.

20:28.217 --> 20:31.051
And where have <i>you</i> been?

20:31.053 --> 20:33.186
Ugh. In the editing room.

20:33.188 --> 20:34.888
Trying to make something viable

20:34.890 --> 20:38.260
out of your insane
on-camera ramblings.

20:39.894 --> 20:45.698
Paul, do you know that
huge store called Way Mart

20:45.700 --> 20:48.034
or Mall Mart,
something on Cirrillos?

20:48.036 --> 20:50.937
Yeah, of course. It's owned
by some crazy conservatives.

20:50.939 --> 20:52.105
You shouldn't shop there.

20:52.107 --> 20:54.808
I thought it was nirvana.

20:54.810 --> 20:56.878
Everything was so inexpensive.

20:56.880 --> 20:58.579
The effect was intoxicating.

20:58.581 --> 21:02.081
As intoxicating as that
giant tumbler of tequila?

21:02.083 --> 21:05.988
Yes.
But in a different way.

21:07.122 --> 21:09.322
- He should be in bed.
- Why?

21:09.324 --> 21:11.826
Because it's 2:00
in the morning.

21:11.828 --> 21:13.226
He doesn't have school
in the morning.

21:13.228 --> 21:15.428
I know, because
we haven't enrolled him

21:15.430 --> 21:17.997
because we don't know
his name.

21:17.999 --> 21:19.734
Have a tequila.

21:19.736 --> 21:22.069
Oh. I'm so tired.

21:22.071 --> 21:25.606
Oh. I'm so tired.

21:31.346 --> 21:33.045
Hey, kid.

21:33.047 --> 21:35.715
I know you're having fun,
but it's very late.

21:35.717 --> 21:38.987
Why don't you turn off the TV?
Let's get you to bed.

21:40.622 --> 21:42.389
Thanks, buddy.

21:42.391 --> 21:44.193
Mañana, piranha.

21:49.631 --> 21:52.300
Are you mad at me?

21:52.302 --> 21:54.169
Paul?

22:00.442 --> 22:05.811
Getting a nightcap?

22:05.813 --> 22:08.117
Some tea.

22:13.022 --> 22:16.391
Did you see the photo
for the dust jacket?

22:18.861 --> 22:21.161
Yes, I did.

22:21.163 --> 22:23.198
What do you think?

22:25.567 --> 22:27.201
This is why you need me.

22:27.203 --> 22:30.937
You really, really should have
let me look over these

22:30.939 --> 22:32.671
before you chose the cover,

22:32.673 --> 22:39.112
because you look like
a person with a mental handicap.

22:39.114 --> 22:44.319
No creature smiles <i>this</i> hard
in all of nature.

22:46.854 --> 22:50.323
I do.
When you make me laugh.

22:50.325 --> 22:53.395
Oh.

22:54.196 --> 22:55.529
That was cruel.

22:57.265 --> 23:01.137
The kettle's boiling.
So to speak.

23:04.806 --> 23:07.476
Fuck the tea.

23:09.411 --> 23:10.543
Yay.

23:20.622 --> 23:21.888
Well, hello.

23:21.890 --> 23:23.323
I assume the kid
got to you okay.

23:23.325 --> 23:26.292
Yes. Yes, he's here
with me now.

23:26.294 --> 23:27.661
You brought him here?

23:27.663 --> 23:29.396
Yes, of course.
He wants to see you.

23:29.398 --> 23:31.865
What, are you insane?
He can't see me like this.

23:31.867 --> 23:34.601
Don't be ridiculous.

23:34.603 --> 23:36.471
Want a Rolo?

23:40.676 --> 23:42.475
That's littering.

23:42.477 --> 23:43.642
So?

23:43.644 --> 23:46.746
So, we don't do that.

23:46.748 --> 23:48.083
Pick it up.

23:49.185 --> 23:51.187
Pick it up.

23:58.727 --> 24:01.428
Don't bring him back here. It's
gonna screw him up in the head.

24:01.430 --> 24:03.664
Like every decision
you haven't made already

24:03.666 --> 24:04.898
hasn't screwed him up.

24:04.900 --> 24:06.266
Hey, I don't need any shit
from you.

24:06.268 --> 24:07.834
You're going to take it,
young man,

24:07.836 --> 24:09.637
because Paul and I
are looking after your child.

24:09.639 --> 24:13.205
- Who is Paul?
- Paul is my male companion,

24:13.207 --> 24:16.275
and he has been
for the last 10 years.

24:16.277 --> 24:17.944
You have the problem
with that?

24:17.946 --> 24:20.149
No.

24:20.916 --> 24:23.082
Oh.
Well, anyway,

24:23.084 --> 24:24.317
we brought him here

24:24.319 --> 24:26.219
so that
you could see each other

24:26.221 --> 24:27.821
and to reassure you
that he's being

24:27.823 --> 24:30.659
well taken care of
in your absence.

24:33.128 --> 24:34.927
You're welcome.

24:34.929 --> 24:37.398
What would I thank you for?

24:37.400 --> 24:39.331
Where were you
when I was 10 years old?

24:39.333 --> 24:40.634
I could've used you then.

24:40.636 --> 24:41.968
And now you come back here

24:41.970 --> 24:43.637
with your scarf
around your neck and think

24:43.639 --> 24:44.704
you're saving the day?

24:44.706 --> 24:46.372
It's called kerchief.

24:46.374 --> 24:47.840
You're not the hero of me

24:47.842 --> 24:49.042
and my son's story, all right?

24:49.044 --> 24:51.380
You're a last resort.

24:52.313 --> 24:55.215
Wait. What's his name?

24:56.384 --> 24:57.584
I wrote it in the Bible.

24:57.586 --> 24:59.388
Wait. What?

25:05.861 --> 25:08.428
So, it turns out
the county

25:08.430 --> 25:11.631
won't allow visits
from children today.

25:11.633 --> 25:13.132
But the lady out front
said that it was...

25:13.134 --> 25:16.403
Without
additional paperwork.

25:16.405 --> 25:19.142
Oh.

25:20.275 --> 25:22.576
I have a great idea.

25:22.578 --> 25:24.476
Why don't we go
to a video arcade

25:24.478 --> 25:27.380
- and then get some ice cream?
- Yeah.

25:27.382 --> 25:30.451
Or we could go to
the Georgia O'Keeffe Museum,

25:30.453 --> 25:33.289
and afterwards
have a nice salad.

25:34.823 --> 25:36.689
- Yes! Yes!
- Yes! Fuck you!

25:36.691 --> 25:39.193
- You saw that, didn't you?!
- Nice shot! Nice shot!

25:39.195 --> 25:42.696
Yes!

25:56.378 --> 25:58.779
Excuse me... sweetheart.

25:58.781 --> 26:02.349
We don't fold throws.
It's too fussy.

26:02.351 --> 26:03.849
We want it be more casual,

26:03.851 --> 26:08.155
so we drape it
like a woman reclining, thus.

26:08.157 --> 26:09.723
Yes, you mustn't make it
seem as if you put

26:09.725 --> 26:11.724
- too much thought into it.
- Exactly so.

26:11.726 --> 26:13.927
It shouldn't look like
it's been placed there.

26:13.929 --> 26:15.596
- It should look like it's...
- Just appeared.

26:15.598 --> 26:17.230
- Yes, like a...
- Cyst.

26:17.232 --> 26:19.567
- ...rainbow or a...
- Cancer cell.

26:19.569 --> 26:21.501
Wildflower.

26:21.503 --> 26:24.070
- Perfect.
- That's wrong.

26:24.072 --> 26:27.209
Excuse us.
Uh. Excuse me.

26:28.176 --> 26:30.810
Look, the Bible.

26:30.812 --> 26:33.647
Hmm.

26:33.649 --> 26:35.349
From Bo, remember?
He said he left a note.

26:35.351 --> 26:37.951
Oh, yeah, sorry.
I thought you'd found God.

26:37.953 --> 26:41.754
Um, "It's Bo. Remember me?
This is grandson.

26:41.756 --> 26:45.591
"Mother is dead.
I got trouble/jail.

26:45.593 --> 26:48.328
Take care of him.
He's Angel."

26:48.330 --> 26:51.197
He's really got something
against articles of speech.

26:51.199 --> 26:52.198
Angel...

26:56.205 --> 26:58.407
Is your name Angel?

27:01.275 --> 27:02.909
Why didn't you tell us?

27:05.813 --> 27:07.813
I don't like it.

27:07.815 --> 27:09.015
No one likes their name.

27:09.017 --> 27:10.317
No, can you imagine
how I felt

27:10.319 --> 27:11.752
on my first day at school
when the teacher

27:11.754 --> 27:13.453
called out
a Erasmus Dickey Brumble?

27:13.455 --> 27:16.391
- What's wrong with Angel?
- It's gay.

27:17.258 --> 27:18.725
It is a little gay.

27:18.727 --> 27:20.627
What would you like
to be called?

27:20.629 --> 27:22.029
Bill.

27:22.031 --> 27:24.130
Then Bill you shall be.

27:24.132 --> 27:26.632
You can't just change his name
because he wants to change it.

27:26.634 --> 27:29.069
- Why not?
- Yeah, why not?

27:29.071 --> 27:32.973
All right, fine, Bill it is.
But one question.

27:32.975 --> 27:35.376
Why didn't you just tell us
you wanted to be called Bill

27:35.378 --> 27:36.510
from the outset?

27:36.512 --> 27:38.344
Because I just thought of it.

27:38.346 --> 27:40.580
I've been trying
to think of a name.

27:40.582 --> 27:42.049
What difference does it make?

27:42.051 --> 27:45.051
It makes a difference
because for two weeks,

27:45.053 --> 27:46.186
we've been calling him "kid"

27:46.188 --> 27:47.486
and we haven't
put him in school.

27:47.488 --> 27:50.256
No problem, just
from now on, communicate.

27:50.258 --> 27:51.791
Yeah, communicate.

27:51.793 --> 27:53.726
Don't, don't, don't, don't!

27:53.728 --> 27:54.794
Don't do that!

27:54.796 --> 27:56.463
All the fucking time
you do that!

27:56.465 --> 27:58.165
You make me look like an idiot

27:58.167 --> 28:00.867
in front of the crew,
in front of the kid!

28:00.869 --> 28:03.535
The kid's got a name.
He's call...

28:03.537 --> 28:04.870
Sorry, what was your name?

28:04.872 --> 28:06.372
It's Bill!

28:06.374 --> 28:09.076
Uh, Paul?
Paul, wait, we need you.

28:12.547 --> 28:16.449
Well, can you make an exception
in my case?

28:16.451 --> 28:18.952
Perhaps it would make a
difference if I was to tell you

28:18.954 --> 28:22.388
my name was Erasmus Bumble.

28:22.390 --> 28:25.926
I present to cookery program
and... Oh, sod it.

28:25.928 --> 28:29.599
Taco Bell don't deliver.
I can't get a hold of Paul.

28:30.865 --> 28:32.933
Hello, Paul, it's me.

28:32.935 --> 28:35.903
You made your point
quite eloquently.

28:35.905 --> 28:37.471
Please come home.

28:40.476 --> 28:46.045
I have made you cochinita pibil
with homemade tortilla.

28:46.047 --> 28:48.447
I've offered
to make you anything

28:48.449 --> 28:52.321
from the finest ingredients
known to man.

28:53.956 --> 28:55.888
Taco Bell.

28:55.890 --> 28:58.826
Fine.

28:58.828 --> 29:00.426
All right.

29:00.428 --> 29:03.332
Total capitulation.

29:08.871 --> 29:10.372
Shit.

29:11.573 --> 29:14.474
This is raccoon.

29:14.476 --> 29:17.343
It's by the building
that's brown,

29:17.345 --> 29:18.611
and its square,

29:18.613 --> 29:20.747
and it has these
little logs on the roof.

29:20.749 --> 29:23.050
In case you hadn't noticed,

29:23.052 --> 29:27.853
you just described every
fucking building in Santa Fe.

29:27.855 --> 29:28.921
Wait, there it is!

29:28.923 --> 29:31.459
Oh, great.

29:38.501 --> 29:41.100
<i>♪♪ I'm glad we made it
To Taco Bell ♪♪</i>

29:41.102 --> 29:43.305
Come on, come on, come on!

29:45.908 --> 29:48.308
Hi, welcome to Taco Bell.
My name's Leticia.

29:48.310 --> 29:49.642
How can I help you?

29:49.644 --> 29:52.344
Hello, Leticia.
My name is Erasmus.

29:52.346 --> 29:54.981
And this is my grandson Bill.

29:54.983 --> 29:56.683
Can I have the Crunch Wrap
Supreme with bacon

29:56.685 --> 29:58.118
and the Nachos BellGrande?

29:58.120 --> 29:59.785
Sure.

30:01.256 --> 30:04.157
And for you, sir?

30:04.159 --> 30:06.559
I'm sorry,
I am mesmerized

30:06.561 --> 30:11.330
by the divergent culinary
concepts at play here.

30:11.332 --> 30:13.533
Cheesy Gordita Crunch.

30:13.535 --> 30:17.803
Fiery Doritos Locos
Tacos Supreme.

30:17.805 --> 30:20.541
I mean, it's like
Mexican jazz music.

30:20.543 --> 30:23.709
- Are you a Erasmus Brumble?
- I am indeed.

30:23.711 --> 30:25.278
I heard that you called earlier.

30:25.280 --> 30:28.682
I love your books
and your TV show, and, well,

30:28.684 --> 30:30.417
what are you doing here?

30:30.419 --> 30:32.552
Well, if you like my books
and my TV show,

30:32.554 --> 30:33.986
what are <i>you</i> doing here?

30:33.988 --> 30:36.823
Are you going
to order something?

30:36.825 --> 30:39.426
I'd love to see
the wine list first, please.

30:41.630 --> 30:43.765
He wasn't joking.

30:48.269 --> 30:49.468
You like it?

30:49.470 --> 30:53.240
Oh, Bill,
I've seen the light.

30:53.242 --> 30:54.741
What?

30:54.743 --> 30:56.776
Well, have a think.

30:56.778 --> 31:00.015
What's the happiest
you've ever been?

31:02.551 --> 31:05.385
One time with my dad,
he took me to the mountains,

31:05.387 --> 31:06.989
and we shot squirrels.

31:08.323 --> 31:10.991
Hmm.

31:10.993 --> 31:17.597
Well, for me, sitting here
sharing this taco with you,

31:17.599 --> 31:19.769
is <i>that</i> good.

31:25.340 --> 31:29.678
But there's got to be
a better table than this.

31:35.749 --> 31:38.820
How long have you been sitting
alone here in the dark?

31:39.653 --> 31:42.054
Uh... 10 years.

31:42.056 --> 31:44.858
It's been a nightmare
since you've been away.

31:44.860 --> 31:46.826
Bill and I have been
crying our eyes out.

31:46.828 --> 31:50.128
- Isn't that right, Bill?
- No, it was fine.

31:50.130 --> 31:51.598
We went to Taco Bell.

31:51.600 --> 31:53.702
Why don't you trot off to bed,
little man?

31:57.805 --> 32:00.307
We can't have a kid.

32:00.309 --> 32:03.242
We are kids.

32:03.244 --> 32:04.778
Well, that's not true.

32:04.780 --> 32:06.779
You're more of a kid
than me.

32:06.781 --> 32:08.782
Do I have a sense of play?

32:08.784 --> 32:11.118
Oh, uh, <i>yeah.</i>

32:13.421 --> 32:15.088
But you're a man.

32:15.090 --> 32:19.458
You're a great big hulking
Paleolithic beast of a man.

32:19.460 --> 32:22.128
You're talking about my ass.

32:22.130 --> 32:23.629
No.

32:23.631 --> 32:25.831
Look at me.

32:25.833 --> 32:30.972
You have the biggest heart
of any man I know.

33:00.735 --> 33:02.871
Is everything all right?

33:07.342 --> 33:09.274
Yes, everything's fine.

33:09.276 --> 33:11.813
Can I have Chunky Monkey?

33:13.148 --> 33:15.150
Yes, of course.

33:16.317 --> 33:17.850
Where is it?

33:17.852 --> 33:20.086
It's in the freezer
in the kitchen.

33:20.088 --> 33:22.591
There isn't any there.
I looked.

33:23.557 --> 33:25.692
No, it's in the freezer
in the garage!

33:25.694 --> 33:27.159
It's in the garage!

33:27.161 --> 33:29.861
The one with all
the Kevin Costner magnets on it!

33:29.863 --> 33:31.164
Who's Kevin "Coster"?

33:31.166 --> 33:33.000
He was in that film.
What was it called?

33:33.002 --> 33:34.567
It doesn't matter.
It doesn't matt...

33:34.569 --> 33:35.936
It's doesn't matter.

33:35.938 --> 33:38.272
It's the only freezer
that's in the garage.

33:38.274 --> 33:39.438
Okay.

33:39.440 --> 33:41.709
Good night.

33:44.246 --> 33:45.444
Do you want some?

33:45.446 --> 33:47.550
No, thank you.

33:48.350 --> 33:50.019
Okay.

33:51.986 --> 33:55.388
Oh, <i>Dances with Wolves!</i>

34:02.930 --> 34:05.167
We gotta make him lunch.

34:07.034 --> 34:09.170
We have to make him lunch.

34:11.773 --> 34:13.943
We have to make him lunch.

34:16.543 --> 34:18.210
<i>Taco Bell.</i>

34:18.213 --> 34:20.612
- Pepperoni pizza.
- No.

34:20.614 --> 34:22.782
Come on, man, look.
It's got...

34:22.784 --> 34:26.952
tongue twisters, jokes,
and more mixed-up fun inside.

34:26.954 --> 34:29.353
No.

34:29.356 --> 34:31.759
Oh, God...

34:34.996 --> 34:36.963
All right.
Last offer.

34:36.965 --> 34:40.998
A 2-pound bag
of Sour Patch Kids for lunch.

34:41.001 --> 34:44.303
Candy is for dessert.

34:44.304 --> 34:46.706
You got all the flavors.

34:46.708 --> 34:48.007
Blue.

34:48.010 --> 34:49.978
Please.

34:58.320 --> 35:01.588
Uh, we're still
serving breakfast.

35:01.590 --> 35:02.821
For how long?

35:02.823 --> 35:05.658
Uh...
Another 45 minutes.

35:05.660 --> 35:07.997
Oh, fuck you.

35:13.869 --> 35:15.401
Has it been
45 minutes yet?

35:15.403 --> 35:18.370
No, it's been two.

35:18.372 --> 35:21.774
I want 20 crunch wraps
with bacon, please.

35:21.776 --> 35:24.611
- Twenty?
- Twenty.

35:24.613 --> 35:25.979
Why'd you get 20 of 'em?

35:25.981 --> 35:27.314
Because I'm gonna freeze them

35:27.316 --> 35:29.651
and then thaw them out
every morning.

35:30.686 --> 35:33.885
That's... not going to work.

35:33.887 --> 35:35.555
And it's weird.

35:35.557 --> 35:38.925
Why can't I just take them
to school in a Taco Bell bag?

35:41.195 --> 35:44.930
Because I've written articles
for <i>Server</i> magazine.

35:44.932 --> 35:48.501
- Do you know what that is?
- No.

35:48.503 --> 35:51.139
Get the fuck out of my car.

36:05.686 --> 36:07.255
Mmm.

36:10.992 --> 36:14.227
So the bartender says,
"No? You don't know?

36:14.229 --> 36:17.396
You walk him
and pitch to the rhino."

36:19.133 --> 36:21.033
Why are you wearing chaps
at dinner?

36:21.035 --> 36:24.070
These used to belong
to Roy Rogers.

36:26.073 --> 36:27.673
- Please.
- Even though

36:27.675 --> 36:29.008
I don't believe
in reincarnation,

36:29.010 --> 36:30.876
I am becoming more
and more convinced

36:30.878 --> 36:33.678
that in a previous life,
I was a cattle rustler.

36:35.284 --> 36:37.249
You just said you don't believe
in reincarnation.

36:37.251 --> 36:39.619
I can rustle cattle.
I roped a steer.

36:39.621 --> 36:41.889
You couldn't rope Ethel Merman.

36:43.392 --> 36:45.892
Bill, do you like the place?

36:45.894 --> 36:47.426
Seriously, tell them
what time you go to bed.

36:47.428 --> 36:48.961
- Whenever I want.
- Oh...

36:48.963 --> 36:52.198
I want Erasmus and Paul
to be my granddaddys.

36:52.200 --> 36:55.635
- You like Erasmus's cooking?
- No, it's gross.

36:57.773 --> 36:59.071
Where is your dad?

36:59.073 --> 37:00.939
He's in jail
